msgctxt "dn9:1.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Long Discourses 9"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn9:2.1"
msgid "Poṭṭhapādasutta"
msgstr "With Poṭṭhapāda"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "dn9:3.1"
msgid "1. Poṭṭhapādaparibbājakavatthu"
msgstr "On the Wanderer Poṭṭhapāda"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.178"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:4.1"
msgid "<span class=\"evam\">Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​</span>"
msgstr "<span class=”evam”>So I have heard.</span>"

msgctxt "dn9:4.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī, in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

# See my note on MN 78.
msgctxt "dn9:4.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena poṭṭhapādo paribbājako samayappavādake tindukācīre "
"ekasālake mallikāya ārāme paṭivasati mahatiyā paribbājakaparisāya saddhiṃ "
"tiṃsamattehi paribbājakasatehi."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the wanderer Poṭṭhapāda was residing together with three "
"hundred wanderers in Mallikā’s single-halled monastery for group debates, "
"set among the flaking pale-moon ebony trees."

msgctxt "dn9:4.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ "
"piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha got dressed in the morning and, taking his bowl and robes, "
"entered Sāvatthī for alms."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to him:"

msgctxt "dn9:5.2"
msgid "“atippago kho tāva sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya carituṃ."
msgstr "“It’s too early to wander for alms in Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "dn9:5.3"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ yena samayappavādako tindukācīro ekasālako mallikāya ārāmo, yena "
"poṭṭhapādo paribbājako tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I go to Mallikā’s monastery to visit the wanderer Poṭṭhapāda?”"

msgctxt "dn9:5.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā yena samayappavādako tindukācīro ekasālako mallikāya ārāmo "
"tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "So that’s what he did."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.179"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:6.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena poṭṭhapādo paribbājako mahatiyā paribbājakaparisāya "
"saddhiṃ nisinno hoti unnādiniyā uccāsaddamahāsaddāya anekavihitaṃ "
"tiracchānakathaṃ kathentiyā."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time, Poṭṭhapāda was sitting together with a large assembly of "
"wanderers making an uproar, a dreadful racket. They engaged in all kinds of "
"unworthy talk, such as"

msgctxt "dn9:6.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:6.3"
msgid ""
"rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ mahāmattakathaṃ senākathaṃ bhayakathaṃ yuddhakathaṃ "
"annakathaṃ pānakathaṃ vatthakathaṃ sayanakathaṃ mālākathaṃ gandhakathaṃ "
"ñātikathaṃ yānakathaṃ gāmakathaṃ nigamakathaṃ nagarakathaṃ janapadakathaṃ "
"itthikathaṃ sūrakathaṃ visikhākathaṃ kumbhaṭṭhānakathaṃ pubbapetakathaṃ "
"nānattakathaṃ lokakkhāyikaṃ samuddakkhāyikaṃ itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā."
msgstr ""
"talk about kings, bandits, and ministers; talk about armies, threats, and "
"wars; talk about food, drink, clothes, and beds; talk about garlands and "
"fragrances; talk about family, vehicles, villages, towns, cities, and "
"countries; talk about women and heroes; street talk and well talk; talk "
"about the departed; motley talk; tales of land and sea; and talk about being "
"reborn in this or that state of existence."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:7.1"
msgid "Addasā kho poṭṭhapādo paribbājako bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ;"
msgstr "Poṭṭhapāda saw the Buddha coming off in the distance,"

msgctxt "dn9:7.2"
msgid "disvāna sakaṃ parisaṃ saṇṭhapesi:"
msgstr "and hushed his own assembly:"

msgctxt "dn9:7.3"
msgid "“appasaddā bhonto hontu, mā bhonto saddamakattha."
msgstr "“Be quiet, good sirs, don’t make a sound."

msgctxt "dn9:7.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ samaṇo gotamo āgacchati."
msgstr "Here comes the ascetic Gotama."

msgctxt "dn9:7.5"
msgid "Appasaddakāmo kho so āyasmā appasaddassa vaṇṇavādī."
msgstr "The venerable likes quiet and praises quiet."

msgctxt "dn9:7.6"
msgid "Appeva nāma appasaddaṃ parisaṃ viditvā upasaṅkamitabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Hopefully if he sees that our assembly is quiet he’ll see fit to approach.”"

msgctxt "dn9:7.7"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te paribbājakā tuṇhī ahesuṃ."
msgstr "Then those wanderers fell silent."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā yena poṭṭhapādo paribbājako tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "Then the Buddha approached Poṭṭhapāda,"

msgctxt "dn9:8.2"
msgid "Atha kho poṭṭhapādo paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "who said to him:"

msgctxt "dn9:8.3"
msgid "“etu kho, bhante, bhagavā."
msgstr "“Come, Blessed One!"

msgctxt "dn9:8.4"
msgid "Svāgataṃ, bhante, bhagavato."
msgstr "Welcome, Blessed One!"

msgctxt "dn9:8.5"
msgid ""
"Cirassaṃ kho, bhante, bhagavā imaṃ pariyāyamakāsi, yadidaṃ idhāgamanāya."
msgstr "It’s been a long time since you took the opportunity to come here."

msgctxt "dn9:8.6"
msgid "Nisīdatu, bhante, bhagavā, idaṃ āsanaṃ paññattan”ti."
msgstr "Please, sir, sit down, this seat is ready.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:9.1"
msgid "Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane."
msgstr "The Buddha sat on the seat spread out,"

msgctxt "dn9:9.2"
msgid ""
"Poṭṭhapādopi kho paribbājako aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "while Poṭṭhapāda took a low seat and sat to one side."

msgctxt "dn9:9.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho poṭṭhapādaṃ paribbājakaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said to him:"

#. VAR: kāya nuttha → kāya nottha (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn9:9.4"
msgid ""
"“kāya nuttha, poṭṭhapāda, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā, kā ca pana vo "
"antarākathā vippakatā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Poṭṭhapāda, what were you sitting talking about just now? What conversation "
"was unfinished?”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn9:10.1"
msgid "1.1. Abhisaññānirodhakathā"
msgstr "On the Cessation of Perception"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.180"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:11.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, poṭṭhapādo paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, the wanderer Poṭṭhapāda said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn9:11.2"
msgid "“tiṭṭhatesā, bhante, kathā, yāya mayaṃ etarahi kathāya sannisinnā."
msgstr "“Sir, leave aside what we were sitting talking about just now."

msgctxt "dn9:11.3"
msgid "Nesā, bhante, kathā bhagavato dullabhā bhavissati pacchāpi savanāya."
msgstr "It won’t be hard for you to hear about that later."

msgctxt "dn9:11.4"
msgid ""
"Purimāni, bhante, divasāni purimatarāni, nānātitthiyānaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ "
"kotūhalasālāya sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ abhisaññānirodhe kathā udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"Sir, a few days ago several ascetics and brahmins who follow various other "
"paths were sitting together at the debating hall, and this discussion came "
"up among them:"

# abhisaññānirodha doesn't appear elsewhere. Comm says: Abhisaññānirodheti ettha abhīti upasaggamattaṃ. Saññānirodheti cittanirodhe … Rendering abhi- here as "higher" or 'ultimate" is, I think, overdetermining it.
msgctxt "dn9:11.5"
msgid "‘kathaṃ nu kho, bho, abhisaññānirodho hotī’ti?"
msgstr "‘How does the cessation of perception happen?’"

msgctxt "dn9:11.6"
msgid "Tatrekacce evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "Some of them said:"

msgctxt "dn9:11.7"
msgid "‘ahetū appaccayā purisassa saññā uppajjantipi nirujjhantipi."
msgstr "‘A person’s perceptions arise and cease without cause or reason."

msgctxt "dn9:11.8"
msgid "Yasmiṃ samaye uppajjanti, saññī tasmiṃ samaye hoti."
msgstr "When they arise, you become percipient."

msgctxt "dn9:11.9"
msgid "Yasmiṃ samaye nirujjhanti, asaññī tasmiṃ samaye hotī’ti."
msgstr "When they cease, you become non-percipient.’"

msgctxt "dn9:11.10"
msgid "Ittheke abhisaññānirodhaṃ paññapenti. <span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr "That’s how some describe the cessation of perception."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:12.1"
msgid "Tamañño evamāha:"
msgstr "But someone else says:"

# For this idiom, cp SN 47.19
#. VAR: pana metaṃ → na kho nāmetaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn9:12.2"
msgid "‘na kho pana metaṃ, bho, evaṃ bhavissati."
msgstr "‘That’s not how it is, gentlemen!"

msgctxt "dn9:12.3"
msgid "Saññā hi, bho, purisassa attā."
msgstr "Perception is a person’s self,"

msgctxt "dn9:12.4"
msgid "Sā ca kho upetipi apetipi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:12.5"
msgid "Yasmiṃ samaye upeti, saññī tasmiṃ samaye hoti."
msgstr "When it enters, you become percipient."

msgctxt "dn9:12.6"
msgid "Yasmiṃ samaye apeti, asaññī tasmiṃ samaye hotī’ti."
msgstr "When it departs, you become non-percipient.’"

msgctxt "dn9:12.7"
msgid "Ittheke abhisaññānirodhaṃ paññapenti. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr "That’s how some describe the cessation of perception."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:13.1"
msgid "Tamañño evamāha:"
msgstr "But someone else says:"

msgctxt "dn9:13.2"
msgid "‘na kho pana metaṃ, bho, evaṃ bhavissati."
msgstr "‘That’s not how it is, gentlemen!"

msgctxt "dn9:13.3"
msgid "Santi hi, bho, samaṇabrāhmaṇā mahiddhikā mahānubhāvā."
msgstr "There are ascetics and brahmins of great power and might."

# These verbs are used in DN 29 in the sense of being able to "take away" or "add to" the sasana.
msgctxt "dn9:13.4"
msgid "Te imassa purisassa saññaṃ upakaḍḍhantipi apakaḍḍhantipi."
msgstr "They insert and extract a person’s perception."

msgctxt "dn9:13.5"
msgid "Yasmiṃ samaye upakaḍḍhanti, saññī tasmiṃ samaye hoti."
msgstr "When they insert it, you become percipient."

msgctxt "dn9:13.6"
msgid "Yasmiṃ samaye apakaḍḍhanti, asaññī tasmiṃ samaye hotī’ti."
msgstr "When they extract it, you become non-percipient.’"

msgctxt "dn9:13.7"
msgid "Ittheke abhisaññānirodhaṃ paññapenti. <span class=\"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr "That’s how some describe the cessation of perception."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:14.1"
msgid "Tamañño evamāha:"
msgstr "But someone else says:"

msgctxt "dn9:14.2"
msgid "‘na kho pana metaṃ, bho, evaṃ bhavissati."
msgstr "‘That’s not how it is, gentlemen!"

msgctxt "dn9:14.3"
msgid "Santi hi, bho, devatā mahiddhikā mahānubhāvā."
msgstr "There are deities of great power and might."

msgctxt "dn9:14.4"
msgid "Tā imassa purisassa saññaṃ upakaḍḍhantipi apakaḍḍhantipi."
msgstr "They insert and extract a person’s perception."

msgctxt "dn9:14.5"
msgid "Yasmiṃ samaye upakaḍḍhanti, saññī tasmiṃ samaye hoti."
msgstr "When they insert it, you become percipient."

msgctxt "dn9:14.6"
msgid "Yasmiṃ samaye apakaḍḍhanti, asaññī tasmiṃ samaye hotī’ti."
msgstr "When they extract it, you become non-percipient.’"

msgctxt "dn9:14.7"
msgid "Ittheke abhisaññānirodhaṃ paññapenti. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr "That’s how some describe the cessation of perception."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:15.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃyeva ārabbha sati udapādi:"
msgstr "That reminded me of the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn9:15.2"
msgid "‘aho nūna bhagavā, aho nūna sugato, yo imesaṃ dhammānaṃ sukusalo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Surely it’s the Blessed One, the Holy One who is so skilled in such "
"matters.’"

# pakataññū is, I think, unique to this passage.
msgctxt "dn9:15.3"
msgid "Bhagavā, bhante, kusalo, bhagavā pakataññū abhisaññānirodhassa."
msgstr "The Buddha is skilled and well-versed in the cessation of perception."

msgctxt "dn9:15.4"
msgid "Kathaṃ nu kho, bhante, abhisaññānirodho hotī”ti?"
msgstr "How does the cessation of perception happen?”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn9:16.1"
msgid "1.2. Sahetukasaññuppādanirodhakathā"
msgstr "Perception Arises With a Cause"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wp" id="wp7"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.181"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:17.1"
msgid "“Tatra, poṭṭhapāda, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "“Regarding this, Poṭṭhapāda, those ascetics and brahmins who say that"

msgctxt "dn9:17.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahetū appaccayā purisassa saññā uppajjantipi nirujjhantipī’ti, āditova "
"tesaṃ aparaddhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"a person’s perceptions arise and cease without cause or reason are wrong "
"from the start."

msgctxt "dn9:17.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn9:17.4"
msgid ""
"Sahetū hi, poṭṭhapāda, sappaccayā purisassa saññā uppajjantipi nirujjhantipi."
msgstr "Because a person’s perceptions arise and cease with cause and reason."

msgctxt "dn9:17.5"
msgid "Sikkhā ekā saññā uppajjati, sikkhā ekā saññā nirujjhati."
msgstr "With training, certain perceptions arise and certain perceptions cease."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.182"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:18.1"
msgid "Kā ca sikkhā”ti?"
msgstr "And what is that training?” said the Buddha."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn9:18.2"
msgid "Bhagavā avoca."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:18.3"
msgid "“Idha, poṭṭhapāda, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ, sammāsambuddho …"
msgstr ""
"“It’s when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened "
"Buddha …"

msgctxt "dn9:18.4"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:18.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, poṭṭhapāda, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti …"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is accomplished in ethics. …"

msgctxt "dn9:18.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:18.7"
msgid ""
"tassime pañcanīvaraṇe pahīne attani samanupassato pāmojjaṃ jāyati, "
"pamuditassa pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ "
"vedeti, sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Seeing that the hindrances have been given up in them, gladness springs up. "
"Being joyful, rapture springs up. When the mind is full of rapture, the body "
"becomes tranquil. When the body is tranquil, they feel bliss. And when "
"blissful, the mind becomes immersed."

msgctxt "dn9:18.8"
msgid ""
"So vivicceva kāmehi, vivicca akusalehi dhammehi, savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ "
"vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ<a class=\"wp\" id=\"wp9-10\"></a> paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unwholesome qualities, "
"they enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and "
"bliss born of seclusion, while applying the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "dn9:18.9"
msgid "Tassa yā purimā kāmasaññā, sā nirujjhati."
msgstr "The sensual perception that they had previously ceases."

msgctxt "dn9:18.10"
msgid ""
"Vivekajapītisukhasukhumasaccasaññā tasmiṃ samaye hoti, "
"vivekajapītisukhasukhumasaccasaññīyeva tasmiṃ samaye hoti."
msgstr ""
"At that time they have a subtle and true perception of the rapture and bliss "
"born of seclusion."

msgctxt "dn9:18.11"
msgid "Evampi sikkhā ekā saññā uppajjati, sikkhā ekā saññā nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"That’s how, with training, certain perceptions arise and certain perceptions "
"cease."

msgctxt "dn9:18.12"
msgid "Ayaṃ sikkhā”ti bhagavā avoca."
msgstr "And this is that training,” said the Buddha."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wp" id="wp11"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.183"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:19.1"
msgid ""
"“Puna caparaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ "
"sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ "
"dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"“Furthermore, as the applying of the mind and keeping it connected are "
"stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and "
"confidence, and unified mind, without applying the mind and keeping it "
"connected. "

msgctxt "dn9:19.2"
msgid "Tassa yā purimā vivekajapītisukhasukhumasaccasaññā, sā nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"The subtle and true perception of the rapture and bliss born of seclusion "
"that they had previously ceases."

msgctxt "dn9:19.3"
msgid ""
"Samādhijapītisukhasukhumasaccasaññā tasmiṃ samaye hoti, "
"samādhijapītisukhasukhumasaccasaññīyeva tasmiṃ samaye hoti."
msgstr ""
"At that time they have a subtle and true perception of the rapture and bliss "
"born of immersion."

msgctxt "dn9:19.4"
msgid "Evampi sikkhā ekā saññā uppajjati, sikkhā ekā saññā nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"That’s how, with training, certain perceptions arise and certain perceptions "
"cease."

msgctxt "dn9:19.5"
msgid "Ayampi sikkhā”ti bhagavā avoca."
msgstr "And this is that training,” said the Buddha."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wp" id="wp12"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:20.1"
msgid ""
"“Puna caparaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati "
"sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti:"
msgstr ""
"“Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and "
"remains in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, "
"mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones "
"declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss’. "

msgctxt "dn9:20.2"
msgid "‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti, tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:20.3"
msgid "Tassa yā purimā samādhijapītisukhasukhumasaccasaññā, sā nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"The subtle and true perception of the rapture and bliss born of immersion "
"that they had previously ceases."

msgctxt "dn9:20.4"
msgid ""
"Upekkhāsukhasukhumasaccasaññā tasmiṃ samaye hoti, "
"upekkhāsukhasukhumasaccasaññīyeva tasmiṃ samaye hoti."
msgstr ""
"At that time they have a subtle and true perception of equanimous bliss."

msgctxt "dn9:20.5"
msgid "Evampi sikkhā ekā saññā uppajjati, sikkhā ekā saññā nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"That’s how, with training, certain perceptions arise and certain perceptions "
"cease."

msgctxt "dn9:20.6"
msgid "Ayampi sikkhā”ti bhagavā avoca."
msgstr "And this is that training,” said the Buddha."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wp" id="wp13"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:21.1"
msgid ""
"“Puna caparaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā "
"pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ "
"upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"“Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and "
"sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without "
"pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. "

msgctxt "dn9:21.2"
msgid "Tassa yā purimā upekkhāsukhasukhumasaccasaññā, sā nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"The subtle and true perception of equanimous bliss that they had previously "
"ceases."

msgctxt "dn9:21.3"
msgid ""
"Adukkhamasukhasukhumasaccasaññā tasmiṃ samaye hoti, "
"adukkhamasukhasukhumasaccasaññīyeva tasmiṃ samaye hoti."
msgstr "At that time they have a subtle and true perception of neutral feeling."

msgctxt "dn9:21.4"
msgid "Evampi sikkhā ekā saññā uppajjati, sikkhā ekā saññā nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"That’s how, with training, certain perceptions arise and certain perceptions "
"cease."

msgctxt "dn9:21.5"
msgid "Ayampi sikkhā”ti bhagavā avoca."
msgstr "And this is that training,” said the Buddha."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wp" id="wp14"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:22.1"
msgid ""
"“Puna caparaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā "
"paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti "
"ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"“Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with "
"the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of "
"diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the "
"dimension of infinite space."

#. VAR: purimā rūpasaññā → purimasaññā (mr)
msgctxt "dn9:22.2"
msgid "Tassa yā purimā rūpasaññā, sā nirujjhati."
msgstr "The perception of luminous form that they had previously ceases."

msgctxt "dn9:22.3"
msgid ""
"Ākāsānañcāyatanasukhumasaccasaññā tasmiṃ samaye hoti, "
"ākāsānañcāyatanasukhumasaccasaññīyeva tasmiṃ samaye hoti."
msgstr ""
"At that time they have a subtle and true perception of the dimension of "
"infinite space."

msgctxt "dn9:22.4"
msgid "Evampi sikkhā ekā saññā uppajjati, sikkhā ekā saññā nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"That’s how, with training, certain perceptions arise and certain perceptions "
"cease."

msgctxt "dn9:22.5"
msgid "Ayampi sikkhā”ti bhagavā avoca."
msgstr "And this is that training,” said the Buddha."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wp" id="wp15"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.184"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:23.1"
msgid ""
"“Puna caparaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘"
"anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"“Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite "
"space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, enters and remains in the "
"dimension of infinite consciousness."

msgctxt "dn9:23.2"
msgid "Tassa yā purimā ākāsānañcāyatanasukhumasaccasaññā, sā nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"The subtle and true perception of the dimension of infinite space that they "
"had previously ceases."

msgctxt "dn9:23.3"
msgid ""
"Viññāṇañcāyatanasukhumasaccasaññā tasmiṃ samaye hoti, "
"viññāṇañcāyatanasukhumasaccasaññīyeva tasmiṃ samaye hoti."
msgstr ""
"At that time they have a subtle and true perception of the dimension of "
"infinite consciousness."

msgctxt "dn9:23.4"
msgid "Evampi sikkhā ekā saññā uppajjati, sikkhā ekā saññā nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"That’s how, with training, certain perceptions arise and certain perceptions "
"cease."

msgctxt "dn9:23.5"
msgid "Ayampi sikkhā”ti bhagavā avoca."
msgstr "And this is that training,” said the Buddha."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wp" id="wp16"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:24.1"
msgid ""
"“Puna caparaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, bhikkhu sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘"
"natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"“Furthermore, a mendicant—going totally beyond the dimension of infinite "
"consciousness—aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, enters and remains in "
"the dimension of nothingness."

msgctxt "dn9:24.2"
msgid "Tassa yā purimā viññāṇañcāyatanasukhumasaccasaññā, sā nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"The subtle and true perception of the dimension of infinite consciousness "
"that they had previously ceases."

msgctxt "dn9:24.3"
msgid ""
"Ākiñcaññāyatanasukhumasaccasaññā tasmiṃ samaye hoti, "
"ākiñcaññāyatanasukhumasaccasaññīyeva tasmiṃ samaye hoti."
msgstr ""
"At that time they have a subtle and true perception of the dimension of "
"nothingness."

msgctxt "dn9:24.4"
msgid "Evampi sikkhā ekā saññā uppajjati, sikkhā ekā saññā nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"That’s how, with training, certain perceptions arise and certain perceptions "
"cease."

msgctxt "dn9:24.5"
msgid "Ayampi sikkhā”ti bhagavā avoca."
msgstr "And this is that training,” said the Buddha."

# For sakasaññī, see Pj2, "perceives it as his own".
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wp" id="wp17"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:25.1"
msgid ""
"“Yato kho, poṭṭhapāda, bhikkhu idha sakasaññī hoti, so tato amutra tato "
"amutra anupubbena saññaggaṃ phusati."
msgstr ""
"“Poṭṭhapāda, from the time a mendicant here takes responsibility for their "
"own perception, they proceed from one stage to the next, gradually reaching "
"the peak of perception."

msgctxt "dn9:25.2"
msgid "Tassa saññagge ṭhitassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "Standing on the peak of perception they think:"

msgctxt "dn9:25.3"
msgid "‘cetayamānassa me pāpiyo, acetayamānassa me seyyo."
msgstr "‘Intentionality is bad for me, it’s better to be free of it."

msgctxt "dn9:25.4"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana ceteyyaṃ, abhisaṅkhareyyaṃ, imā ca me saññā nirujjheyyuṃ, "
"aññā ca oḷārikā saññā uppajjeyyuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"For if I was to intend and choose, these perceptions would cease in me, and "
"other coarser perceptions would arise."

msgctxt "dn9:25.5"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ na ceva ceteyyaṃ na ca abhisaṅkhareyyan’ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I neither make a choice nor form an intention?’"

msgctxt "dn9:25.6"
msgid "So na ceva ceteti, na ca abhisaṅkharoti."
msgstr "They neither make a choice nor form an intention."

msgctxt "dn9:25.7"
msgid ""
"Tassa acetayato anabhisaṅkharoto tā ceva saññā nirujjhanti, aññā ca oḷārikā "
"saññā na uppajjanti."
msgstr ""
"Those perceptions cease in them, and other coarser perceptions don’t arise."

msgctxt "dn9:25.8"
msgid "So nirodhaṃ phusati."
msgstr "They touch cessation."

msgctxt "dn9:25.9"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, poṭṭhapāda, anupubbābhisaññānirodhasampajānasamāpatti hoti."
msgstr ""
"And that, Poṭṭhapāda, is how the gradual cessation of perception is attained "
"with awareness."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wp" id="wp18"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.185"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:26.1"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, poṭṭhapāda, api nu te ito pubbe evarūpā "
"anupubbābhisaññānirodhasampajānasamāpatti sutapubbā”ti?"
msgstr "What do you think, Poṭṭhapāda? Have you ever heard of this before?”"

msgctxt "dn9:26.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“No, sir."

msgctxt "dn9:26.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavato bhāsitaṃ ājānāmi:"
msgstr "This is how I understand what the Buddha said:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn9:26.4"
msgid ""
"‘yato kho, poṭṭhapāda, bhikkhu idha sakasaññī hoti, so tato amutra tato "
"amutra anupubbena saññaggaṃ phusati, tassa saññagge ṭhitassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr ""
"‘From the time a mendicant here takes responsibility for their own "
"perception, they proceed from one stage to the next, gradually reaching the "
"peak of perception. Standing on the peak of perception they think:"

msgctxt "dn9:26.5"
msgid "“cetayamānassa me pāpiyo, acetayamānassa me seyyo."
msgstr "“Intentionality is bad for me, it’s better to be free of it."

msgctxt "dn9:26.6"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana ceteyyaṃ abhisaṅkhareyyaṃ, imā ca me saññā nirujjheyyuṃ, "
"aññā ca oḷārikā saññā uppajjeyyuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"For if I was to intend and choose, these perceptions would cease in me, and "
"other coarser perceptions would arise."

msgctxt "dn9:26.7"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ na ceva ceteyyaṃ, na ca abhisaṅkhareyyan”ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I neither make a choice nor form an intention?”"

msgctxt "dn9:26.8"
msgid ""
"So na ceva ceteti, na cābhisaṅkharoti, tassa acetayato anabhisaṅkharoto tā "
"ceva saññā nirujjhanti, aññā ca oḷārikā saññā na uppajjanti."
msgstr ""
"Those perceptions cease in them, and other coarser perceptions don’t arise."

msgctxt "dn9:26.9"
msgid "So nirodhaṃ phusati."
msgstr "They reach cessation."

msgctxt "dn9:26.10"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, poṭṭhapāda, anupubbābhisaññānirodhasampajānasamāpatti hotī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"And that is how the gradual cessation of perception is attained with "
"awareness.’”"

msgctxt "dn9:26.11"
msgid "“Evaṃ, poṭṭhapādā”ti."
msgstr "“That’s right, Poṭṭhapāda.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wp" id="wp19"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:27.1"
msgid ""
"“Ekaññeva nu kho, bhante, bhagavā saññaggaṃ paññapeti, udāhu puthūpi "
"saññagge paññapetī”ti?"
msgstr "“Does the Buddha describe just one peak of perception, or many?”"

msgctxt "dn9:27.2"
msgid ""
"“Ekampi kho ahaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, saññaggaṃ paññapemi, puthūpi saññagge "
"paññapemī”ti."
msgstr "“I describe the peak of perception as both one and many.”"

msgctxt "dn9:27.3"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bhante, bhagavā ekampi saññaggaṃ paññapeti, puthūpi "
"saññagge paññapetī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But how, sir, do you describe it as one, and how do you describe it as "
"many?”"

msgctxt "dn9:27.4"
msgid ""
"“Yathā yathā kho, poṭṭhapāda, nirodhaṃ phusati tathā tathāhaṃ saññaggaṃ "
"paññapemi."
msgstr ""
"“I describe the peak of perception according to the specific manner in which "
"one reaches cessation."

msgctxt "dn9:27.5"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho ahaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, ekampi saññaggaṃ paññapemi, puthūpi saññagge "
"paññapemī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how I describe the peak of perception as both one and many.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="wp" id="wp20"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:28.1"
msgid ""
"“Saññā nu kho, bhante, paṭhamaṃ uppajjati, pacchā ñāṇaṃ, udāhu ñāṇaṃ "
"paṭhamaṃ uppajjati, pacchā saññā, udāhu saññā ca ñāṇañca apubbaṃ acarimaṃ "
"uppajjantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, does perception arise first and knowledge afterwards? Or does "
"knowledge arise first and perception afterwards? Or do they both arise at "
"the same time?”"

msgctxt "dn9:28.2"
msgid ""
"“Saññā kho, poṭṭhapāda, paṭhamaṃ uppajjati, pacchā ñāṇaṃ, saññuppādā ca pana "
"ñāṇuppādo hoti."
msgstr ""
"“Perception arises first and knowledge afterwards. The arising of perception "
"leads to the arising of knowledge."

msgctxt "dn9:28.3"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "They understand:"

msgctxt "dn9:28.4"
msgid "‘idappaccayā kira me ñāṇaṃ udapādī’ti."
msgstr "‘My knowledge arose from a specific condition.’"

msgctxt "dn9:28.5"
msgid "Iminā kho etaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ—"
msgstr "That is a way to understand how"

msgctxt "dn9:28.6"
msgid ""
"yathā saññā paṭhamaṃ uppajjati, pacchā ñāṇaṃ, saññuppādā ca pana ñāṇuppādo "
"hotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"perception arises first and knowledge afterwards; that the arising of "
"perception leads to the arising of knowledge.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn9:29.1"
msgid "1.3. Saññāattakathā"
msgstr "Perception and the Self"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="wp" id="wp21"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.186"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:30.1"
msgid "“Saññā nu kho, bhante, purisassa attā, udāhu aññā saññā añño attā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, is perception a person’s self, or are perception and self different "
"things?”"

msgctxt "dn9:30.2"
msgid "“Kaṃ pana tvaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, attānaṃ paccesī”ti?"
msgstr "“But Poṭṭhapāda, do you believe in a self?”"

msgctxt "dn9:30.3"
msgid ""
"“Oḷārikaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, attānaṃ paccemi rūpiṃ cātumahābhūtikaṃ "
"kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I believe in a substantial self, sir, which is physical, made up of the "
"four primary elements, and consumes solid food.”"

msgctxt "dn9:30.4"
msgid ""
"“Oḷāriko ca hi te, poṭṭhapāda, attā abhavissa rūpī cātumahābhūtiko "
"kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkho."
msgstr ""
"“Suppose there was such a substantial self. In that case, perception would "
"be one thing, the self another."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn9:30.5"
msgid "Evaṃ santaṃ kho te, poṭṭhapāda, aññāva saññā bhavissati añño attā."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:30.6"
msgid ""
"Tadamināpetaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā aññāva saññā "
"bhavissati añño attā."
msgstr ""
"Here is another way to understand how perception and self are different "
"things."

# Here titthateva is not "leaving aside", but as per MN 107, which also has a titthateva … atha construction.
#. VAR: Tiṭṭhateva sāyaṃ → tiṭṭhateva ayaṃ (s1-3) | tiṭṭhatevāyaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn9:30.7"
msgid ""
"Tiṭṭhateva sāyaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, oḷāriko attā rūpī cātumahābhūtiko "
"kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkho, atha imassa purisassa aññā ca saññā uppajjanti, aññā "
"ca saññā nirujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"So long as that substantial self remains, still some perceptions arise in a "
"person and others cease."

msgctxt "dn9:30.8"
msgid ""
"Iminā kho etaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā aññāva saññā "
"bhavissati añño attā”ti."
msgstr ""
"That is a way to understand how perception and self are different things.”"

# All manuscripts appear to be missing rūpī, which occurs in the corresponding passage on the attapatilabha
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="wp" id="wp22"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:31.1"
msgid ""
"“Manomayaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, attānaṃ paccemi sabbaṅgapaccaṅgiṃ "
"ahīnindriyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I believe in a mind-made self which is complete in all its various parts, "
"not deficient in any faculty.”"

msgctxt "dn9:31.2"
msgid ""
"“Manomayo ca hi te, poṭṭhapāda, attā abhavissa sabbaṅgapaccaṅgī ahīnindriyo, "
"evaṃ santampi kho te, poṭṭhapāda, aññāva saññā bhavissati añño attā."
msgstr ""
"“Suppose there was such a mind-made self. In that case, perception would be "
"one thing, the self another."

msgctxt "dn9:31.3"
msgid ""
"Tadamināpetaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā aññāva saññā "
"bhavissati añño attā."
msgstr ""
"Here is another way to understand how perception and self are different "
"things."

msgctxt "dn9:31.4"
msgid ""
"Tiṭṭhateva sāyaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, manomayo attā sabbaṅgapaccaṅgī ahīnindriyo, "
"atha imassa purisassa aññā ca saññā uppajjanti, aññā ca saññā nirujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"So long as that mind-made self remains, still some perceptions arise in a "
"person and others cease."

msgctxt "dn9:31.5"
msgid ""
"Imināpi kho etaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā aññāva saññā "
"bhavissati añño attā”ti."
msgstr ""
"That too is a way to understand how perception and self are different "
"things.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wp" id="wp23"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.187"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:32.1"
msgid "“Arūpiṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, attānaṃ paccemi saññāmayan”ti."
msgstr "“I believe in a non-physical self which is made of perception.”"

msgctxt "dn9:32.2"
msgid ""
"“Arūpī ca hi te, poṭṭhapāda, attā abhavissa saññāmayo, evaṃ santampi kho te, "
"poṭṭhapāda, aññāva saññā bhavissati añño attā."
msgstr ""
"“Suppose there was such a non-physical self. In that case, perception would "
"be one thing, the self another."

msgctxt "dn9:32.3"
msgid ""
"Tadamināpetaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā aññāva saññā "
"bhavissati añño attā."
msgstr ""
"Here is another way to understand how perception and self are different "
"things."

msgctxt "dn9:32.4"
msgid ""
"Tiṭṭhateva sāyaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, arūpī attā saññāmayo, atha imassa purisassa "
"aññā ca saññā uppajjanti, aññā ca saññā nirujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"So long as that non-physical self remains, still some perceptions arise in a "
"person and others cease."

msgctxt "dn9:32.5"
msgid ""
"Imināpi kho etaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā aññāva saññā "
"bhavissati añño attā”ti."
msgstr ""
"That too is a way to understand how perception and self are different "
"things.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="wp" id="wp24"></a>
#. VAR: etaṃ → evaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "dn9:33.1"
msgid "“Sakkā panetaṃ, bhante, mayā ñātuṃ:"
msgstr "“But am I able to know whether"

msgctxt "dn9:33.2"
msgid "‘saññā purisassa attā’ti vā ‘aññāva saññā añño attā’ti vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"perception is a person’s self, or whether perception and self are different "
"things?”"

msgctxt "dn9:33.3"
msgid ""
"“Dujjānaṃ kho etaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, tayā aññadiṭṭhikena aññakhantikena "
"aññarucikena aññatrāyogena aññatrācariyakena:"
msgstr ""
"“It’s hard for you to understand this, since you have a different view, "
"creed, belief, practice, and tradition.”"

msgctxt "dn9:33.4"
msgid "‘saññā purisassa attā’ti vā, ‘aññāva saññā añño attāti’ vā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="wp" id="wp25"></a>
#. VAR: aññatrāyogena → aññattha āyogena (s1-3) | anñatrayogena (^mn72#17
#. [Aggi­vaccha­sutta])
msgctxt "dn9:34.1"
msgid ""
"“Sacetaṃ, bhante, mayā dujjānaṃ aññadiṭṭhikena aññakhantikena aññarucikena "
"aññatrāyogena aññatrācariyakena:"
msgstr "“Well, if that’s the case, sir,"

msgctxt "dn9:34.2"
msgid "‘saññā purisassa attā’ti vā, ‘aññāva saññā añño attā’ti vā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:34.3"
msgid "kiṃ pana, bhante, ‘sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"then is this right: ‘The cosmos is eternal. This is the only truth, anything "
"else is wrong’?”"

msgctxt "dn9:34.4"
msgid "“Abyākataṃ kho etaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, mayā:"
msgstr "“This has not been declared by me, Poṭṭhapāda.”"

msgctxt "dn9:34.5"
msgid "‘sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="wp" id="wp26"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:35.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana, bhante, ‘asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Then is this right: ‘The cosmos is not eternal. This is the only truth, "
"anything else is wrong’?”"

msgctxt "dn9:35.2"
msgid "“Etampi kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā abyākataṃ:"
msgstr "“This too has not been declared by me.”"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn9:35.3"
msgid "‘asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti."
msgstr " "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="wp" id="wp27"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.188"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:36.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana, bhante, ‘antavā loko …"
msgstr "“Then is this right: ‘The cosmos is finite …’ …"

msgctxt "dn9:36.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:36.3"
msgid "‘anantavā loko …"
msgstr "‘The cosmos is infinite …’ …"

msgctxt "dn9:36.4"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ …"
msgstr "‘The soul and the body are the same thing …’ …"

msgctxt "dn9:36.5"
msgid "‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ …"
msgstr "‘The soul and the body are different things …’ …"

msgctxt "dn9:36.6"
msgid "‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …"
msgstr "‘A Realized One exists after death …’ …"

msgctxt "dn9:36.7"
msgid "‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …"
msgstr "“A Realized One doesn’t exist after death …” …"

msgctxt "dn9:36.8"
msgid "‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …"
msgstr "“A Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death …” …"

msgctxt "dn9:36.9"
msgid ""
"‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist death. This is the only "
"truth, anything else is wrong’?”"

msgctxt "dn9:36.10"
msgid "“Etampi kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā abyākataṃ:"
msgstr "“This too has not been declared by me.”"

msgctxt "dn9:36.11"
msgid ""
"‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="wp" id="wp28"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.189"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:37.1"
msgid "“Kasmā panetaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā abyākatan”ti?"
msgstr "“Why haven’t these things been declared by the Buddha?”"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn9:37.2"
msgid ""
"“Na hetaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, atthasaṃhitaṃ na dhammasaṃhitaṃ nādibrahmacariyakaṃ, "
"na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na "
"sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, tasmā etaṃ mayā abyākatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Because they’re not beneficial or relevant to the fundamentals of the "
"spiritual life. They don’t lead to disillusionment, fading away, cessation, "
"peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. That’s why I haven’t declared "
"them.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="wp" id="wp29"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:38.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana, bhante, bhagavatā byākatan”ti?"
msgstr "“Then what has been declared by the Buddha?”"

msgctxt "dn9:38.2"
msgid "“Idaṃ dukkhanti kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā byākataṃ."
msgstr ""
"“I have declared this: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of "
"suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice "
"that leads to the cessation of suffering’.”"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn9:38.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ dukkhasamudayoti kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā byākataṃ."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:38.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ dukkhanirodhoti kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā byākataṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:38.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadāti kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā byākatan”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a><a class="wp" id="wp30"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:39.1"
msgid "“Kasmā panetaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā byākatan”ti?"
msgstr "“Why have these things been declared by the Buddha?”"

msgctxt "dn9:39.2"
msgid ""
"“Etañhi, poṭṭhapāda, atthasaṃhitaṃ, etaṃ dhammasaṃhitaṃ, etaṃ "
"ādibrahmacariyakaṃ, etaṃ nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya "
"sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati;"
msgstr ""
"“Because they are beneficial and relevant to the fundamentals of the "
"spiritual life. They lead to disillusionment, fading away, cessation, peace, "
"insight, awakening, and extinguishment."

msgctxt "dn9:39.3"
msgid "tasmā etaṃ mayā byākatan”ti."
msgstr "That’s why I have declared them.”"

msgctxt "dn9:39.4"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, bhagavā, evametaṃ, sugata."
msgstr "“That’s so true, Blessed One! That’s so true, Holy One!"

msgctxt "dn9:39.5"
msgid "Yassadāni, bhante, bhagavā kālaṃ maññatī”ti."
msgstr "Please, sir, go when you’re ready.” "

msgctxt "dn9:39.6"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr "Then the Buddha got up from his seat and left."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="wp" id="wp31"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.190"></a>
#. VAR: vācā → vācāya (si, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn9:40.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te paribbājakā acirapakkantassa bhagavato poṭṭhapādaṃ paribbājakaṃ "
"samantato vācā sannitodakena sañjhabbharimakaṃsu:"
msgstr ""
"Soon after the Buddha left, those wanderers gave Poṭṭhapāda a comprehensive "
"tongue-lashing:"

msgctxt "dn9:40.2"
msgid ""
"“evameva panāyaṃ bhavaṃ poṭṭhapādo yaññadeva samaṇo gotamo bhāsati, taṃ "
"tadevassa abbhanumodati:"
msgstr "“No matter what the ascetic Gotama says, Poṭṭhapāda agrees with him:"

msgctxt "dn9:40.3"
msgid "‘evametaṃ, bhagavā, evametaṃ, sugatā’ti."
msgstr "‘That’s so true, Blessed One! That’s so true, Holy One!’"

msgctxt "dn9:40.4"
msgid ""
"Na kho pana mayaṃ kiñci samaṇassa gotamassa ekaṃsikaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ "
"ājānāma:"
msgstr ""
"We understand that the ascetic Gotama didn’t make any definitive statement "
"at all regarding whether the cosmos is eternal and so on.”"

msgctxt "dn9:40.5"
msgid ""
"‘sassato loko’ti vā, ‘asassato loko’ti vā, ‘antavā loko’ti vā, ‘anantavā "
"loko’ti vā, ‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā, ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vā, ‘"
"hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘"
"hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘neva hoti na na hoti "
"tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:41.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, poṭṭhapādo paribbājako te paribbājake etadavoca:"
msgstr "When they said this, Poṭṭhapāda said to them:"

msgctxt "dn9:41.2"
msgid ""
"“ahampi kho, bho, na kiñci samaṇassa gotamassa ekaṃsikaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ "
"ājānāmi:"
msgstr ""
"“I too understand that the ascetic Gotama didn’t make any definitive "
"statement at all regarding whether the cosmos is eternal and so on."

msgctxt "dn9:41.3"
msgid "‘sassato loko’ti vā, ‘asassato loko’ti vā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:41.4"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:41.5"
msgid "‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:41.6"
msgid ""
"api ca samaṇo gotamo bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ tathaṃ paṭipadaṃ paññapeti "
"dhammaṭṭhitataṃ dhammaniyāmataṃ."
msgstr ""
"Nevertheless, the practice that he describes is true, real, and accurate. It "
"is the regularity of natural principles, the invariance of natural "
"principles."

msgctxt "dn9:41.7"
msgid ""
"Bhūtaṃ kho pana tacchaṃ tathaṃ paṭipadaṃ paññapentassa dhammaṭṭhitataṃ "
"dhammaniyāmataṃ, kathañhi nāma mādiso viññū samaṇassa gotamassa subhāsitaṃ "
"subhāsitato nābbhanumodeyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"So how could a sensible person such as I not agree that what was well spoken "
"by the ascetic Gotama was in fact well spoken?”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn9:42.1"
msgid "2. Cittahatthisāriputtapoṭṭhapādavatthu"
msgstr "On Citta Hatthisāriputta"

# RD, MW, Thanissaro, and DPPN all say "son of an elephant trainer". But this seems to assume a form hatthisarathiputta. Am I missing something?
#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a><a class="wp" id="wp32"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.191"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:43.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho dvīhatīhassa accayena citto ca hatthisāriputto poṭṭhapādo ca "
"paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"Then after two or three days had passed, Citta Hatthisāriputta and "
"Poṭṭhapāda went to see the Buddha."

msgctxt "dn9:43.2"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā citto hatthisāriputto bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "Citta Hatthisāriputta bowed and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "dn9:43.3"
msgid "Poṭṭhapādo pana paribbājako bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr "But the wanderer Poṭṭhapāda exchanged greetings with the Buddha,"

msgctxt "dn9:43.4"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"and when the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side."

msgctxt "dn9:43.5"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho poṭṭhapādo paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Poṭṭhapāda told the Buddha what had happened after he left. The Buddha said:"

msgctxt "dn9:43.6"
msgid ""
"“tadā maṃ, bhante, te paribbājakā acirapakkantassa bhagavato samantato "
"vācāsannitodakena sañjhabbharimakaṃsu:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:43.7"
msgid ""
"‘evameva panāyaṃ bhavaṃ poṭṭhapādo yaññadeva samaṇo gotamo bhāsati, taṃ "
"tadevassa abbhanumodati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:43.8"
msgid "“evametaṃ, bhagavā, evametaṃ, sugatā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:43.9"
msgid ""
"Na kho pana mayaṃ kiñci samaṇassa gotamassa ekaṃsikaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ "
"ājānāma:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:43.10"
msgid ""
"“sassato loko”ti vā, “asassato loko”ti vā, “antavā loko”ti vā, “anantavā "
"loko”ti vā, “taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran”ti vā, “aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran”ti vā, “"
"hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā, “na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā, “"
"hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā, “neva hoti na na hoti "
"tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:43.11"
msgid "Evaṃ vuttāhaṃ, bhante, te paribbājake etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:43.12"
msgid ""
"‘ahampi kho, bho, na kiñci samaṇassa gotamassa ekaṃsikaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ "
"ājānāmi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:43.13"
msgid "“sassato loko”ti vā, “asassato loko”ti vā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:43.14"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:43.15"
msgid "“neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:43.16"
msgid ""
"api ca samaṇo gotamo bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ tathaṃ paṭipadaṃ paññapeti "
"dhammaṭṭhitataṃ dhammaniyāmataṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:43.17"
msgid ""
"Bhūtaṃ kho pana tacchaṃ tathaṃ paṭipadaṃ paññapentassa dhammaṭṭhitataṃ "
"dhammaniyāmataṃ, kathañhi nāma mādiso viññū samaṇassa gotamassa subhāsitaṃ "
"subhāsitato nābbhanumodeyyā’”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a><a class="wp" id="wp33"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:44.1"
msgid "“Sabbeva kho ete, poṭṭhapāda, paribbājakā andhā acakkhukā;"
msgstr "“All those wanderers, Poṭṭhapāda, are blind and sightless."

msgctxt "dn9:44.2"
msgid "tvaṃyeva nesaṃ eko cakkhumā."
msgstr "You are the only one who sees."

msgctxt "dn9:44.3"
msgid "Ekaṃsikāpi hi kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā dhammā desitā paññattā;"
msgstr "For I have taught and pointed out both things that are definitive"

msgctxt "dn9:44.4"
msgid "anekaṃsikāpi hi kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā dhammā desitā paññattā."
msgstr "and things that are not definitive."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:45.1"
msgid "Katame ca te, poṭṭhapāda, mayā anekaṃsikā dhammā desitā paññattā?"
msgstr "And what things have I taught and pointed out that are not definitive?"

#. VAR: loko’ti → lokoti vā (bj, mr)
msgctxt "dn9:45.2"
msgid ""
"‘Sassato loko’ti kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā anekaṃsiko dhammo desito paññatto;"
msgstr "‘The cosmos is eternal’ …"

msgctxt "dn9:45.3"
msgid ""
"‘asassato loko’ti kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā anekaṃsiko dhammo desito paññatto;"
msgstr "‘The cosmos is not eternal’ …"

msgctxt "dn9:45.4"
msgid "‘antavā loko’ti kho, poṭṭhapāda …"
msgstr "‘The cosmos is finite’ …"

msgctxt "dn9:45.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:45.6"
msgid "‘anantavā loko’ti kho, poṭṭhapāda …"
msgstr "‘The cosmos is infinite’ …"

msgctxt "dn9:45.7"
msgid "‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti kho, poṭṭhapāda …"
msgstr "‘The soul is the same thing as the body’ …"

msgctxt "dn9:45.8"
msgid "‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti kho, poṭṭhapāda …"
msgstr "‘The soul and the body are different things’ …"

msgctxt "dn9:45.9"
msgid "‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti kho, poṭṭhapāda …"
msgstr "‘A Realized One exists after death’ …"

msgctxt "dn9:45.10"
msgid "na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti kho, poṭṭhapāda …"
msgstr "‘A Realized One doesn’t exist after death’ …"

msgctxt "dn9:45.11"
msgid "‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti kho, poṭṭhapāda …"
msgstr "‘A Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death’ …"

msgctxt "dn9:45.12"
msgid ""
"‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā "
"anekaṃsiko dhammo desito paññatto."
msgstr "‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:46.1"
msgid "Kasmā ca te, poṭṭhapāda, mayā anekaṃsikā dhammā desitā paññattā?"
msgstr ""
"And why haven’t I taught and pointed such things that are not definitive?"

msgctxt "dn9:46.2"
msgid ""
"Na hete, poṭṭhapāda, atthasaṃhitā na dhammasaṃhitā na ādibrahmacariyakā na "
"nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya "
"na nibbānāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"Because those things aren’t beneficial or relevant to the fundamentals of "
"the spiritual life. They don’t lead to disillusionment, fading away, "
"cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment."

msgctxt "dn9:46.3"
msgid "Tasmā te mayā anekaṃsikā dhammā desitā paññattā."
msgstr "That’s why I haven’t taught and pointed them out."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn9:47.1"
msgid "2.1. Ekaṃsikadhammā"
msgstr "Things That Are Definitive"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.192"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:48.1"
msgid "Katame ca te, poṭṭhapāda, mayā ekaṃsikā dhammā desitā paññattā?"
msgstr "And what things have I taught and pointed out that are definitive?"

msgctxt "dn9:48.2"
msgid "Idaṃ dukkhanti kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā ekaṃsiko dhammo desito paññatto."
msgstr ""
"‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the "
"cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation "
"of suffering’.”"

msgctxt "dn9:48.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ dukkhasamudayoti kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā ekaṃsiko dhammo desito paññatto."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:48.4"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ dukkhanirodhoti kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā ekaṃsiko dhammo desito paññatto."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:48.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadāti kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā ekaṃsiko dhammo "
"desito paññatto."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:49.1"
msgid "Kasmā ca te, poṭṭhapāda, mayā ekaṃsikā dhammā desitā paññattā?"
msgstr "And why have I taught and pointed such things that are definitive?"

msgctxt "dn9:49.2"
msgid ""
"Ete hi, poṭṭhapāda, atthasaṃhitā, ete dhammasaṃhitā, ete ādibrahmacariyakā "
"ete nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya "
"saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"Because they are beneficial and relevant to the fundamentals of the "
"spiritual life. They lead to disillusionment, fading away, cessation, peace, "
"insight, awakening, and extinguishment."

msgctxt "dn9:49.3"
msgid "Tasmā te mayā ekaṃsikā dhammā desitā paññattā."
msgstr "That’s why I have taught and pointed them out."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a><a class="wp" id="wp34"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:50.1"
msgid "Santi, poṭṭhapāda, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:"

msgctxt "dn9:50.2"
msgid "‘ekantasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’ti."
msgstr "‘The self is exclusively happy and is sound after death.’ "

msgctxt "dn9:50.3"
msgid "Tyāhaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "I go up to them and say:"

msgctxt "dn9:50.4"
msgid "‘saccaṃ kira tumhe āyasmanto evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "‘Is it really true that this is the venerables’ view?’"

msgctxt "dn9:50.5"
msgid "“ekantasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā”’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn9:50.6"
msgid "Te ce me evaṃ puṭṭhā ‘āmā’ti paṭijānanti."
msgstr "And they answer, ‘Yes’."

msgctxt "dn9:50.7"
msgid "Tyāhaṃ evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "I say to them:"

msgctxt "dn9:50.8"
msgid "‘api pana tumhe āyasmanto ekantasukhaṃ lokaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ viharathā’ti?"
msgstr "‘But do you meditate knowing and seeing an exclusively happy world?’"

msgctxt "dn9:50.9"
msgid "Iti puṭṭhā ‘no’ti vadanti."
msgstr "Asked this, they say, ‘No.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:51.1"
msgid "Tyāhaṃ evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "I say to them:"

#. VAR: sañjānāthā’ti → sampajānāthāti (bj, mr) | sampajānathāpi (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn9:51.2"
msgid ""
"‘api pana tumhe āyasmanto ekaṃ vā rattiṃ ekaṃ vā divasaṃ upaḍḍhaṃ vā rattiṃ "
"upaḍḍhaṃ vā divasaṃ ekantasukhiṃ attānaṃ sañjānāthā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘But have you perceived an exclusively happy self for a single day or night, "
"or even half a day or night?’"

msgctxt "dn9:51.3"
msgid "Iti puṭṭhā ‘no’ti vadanti."
