#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn9:69.1"
msgid "2.2. Tayoattapaṭilābha"
msgstr "Three Kinds of Reincarnation"

# Comm: Tattha attapaṭilābhoti attabhāvapaṭilābho, ettha ca bhagavā tīhi attabhāvapaṭilābhehi tayo bhave dassesi
#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="61"></a><a class="wp" id="wp39"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:70.1"
msgid "“Tayo kho me, poṭṭhapāda, attapaṭilābhā—"
msgstr "“Poṭṭhapāda, there are these three kinds of reincarnation:"

msgctxt "dn9:70.2"
msgid "oḷāriko attapaṭilābho, manomayo attapaṭilābho, arūpo attapaṭilābho."
msgstr ""
"a substantial reincarnation, a mind-made reincarnation, and a non-physical "
"reincarnation."

msgctxt "dn9:70.3"
msgid "Katamo ca, poṭṭhapāda, oḷāriko attapaṭilābho?"
msgstr "And what is a substantial reincarnation?"

msgctxt "dn9:70.4"
msgid "Rūpī cātumahābhūtiko kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkho, ayaṃ oḷāriko attapaṭilābho."
msgstr ""
"It is physical, made up of the four primary elements, and consumes solid "
"food."

msgctxt "dn9:70.5"
msgid "Katamo manomayo attapaṭilābho?"
msgstr "What is a mind-made reincarnation?"

msgctxt "dn9:70.6"
msgid ""
"Rūpī manomayo sabbaṅgapaccaṅgī ahīnindriyo, ayaṃ manomayo attapaṭilābho."
msgstr ""
"It is physical, mind-made, complete in all its various parts, not deficient "
"in any faculty"

msgctxt "dn9:70.7"
msgid "Katamo arūpo attapaṭilābho?"
msgstr "What is a non-physical reincarnation?"

msgctxt "dn9:70.8"
msgid "Arūpī saññāmayo, ayaṃ arūpo attapaṭilābho."
msgstr "It is non-physical, made of perception."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="62"></a><a class="wp" id="wp40"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.196"></a>
msgctxt "dn9:71.1"
msgid ""
"Oḷārikassapi kho ahaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, attapaṭilābhassa pahānāya dhammaṃ desemi:"
msgstr ""
"I teach the Dhamma for the giving up of these three kinds of reincarnation:"

msgctxt "dn9:71.2"
msgid ""
"‘yathāpaṭipannānaṃ vo saṅkilesikā dhammā pahīyissanti, vodāniyā dhammā "
"abhivaḍḍhissanti, paññāpāripūriṃ vepullattañca diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When you practice accordingly, corrupting qualities will be given up in you "
"and cleansing qualities will grow. You’ll enter and remain in the fullness "
"and abundance of wisdom, having realized it with your own insight in this "
"very life.’"

msgctxt "dn9:71.3"
msgid "Siyā kho pana te, poṭṭhapāda, evamassa:"
msgstr "Poṭṭhapāda, you might think: "

# I find the syntax of this passage perplexing. Compare the similar sentiment at SN 22.2, which has a much more clear syntax.
msgctxt "dn9:71.4"
msgid ""
"‘saṅkilesikā dhammā pahīyissanti, vodāniyā dhammā abhivaḍḍhissanti, "
"paññāpāripūriṃ vepullattañca diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharissati, dukkho ca kho vihāro’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Corrupting qualities will be given up and cleansing qualities will grow. "
"One will enter and remain in the fullness and abundance of wisdom, having "
"realized it with one’s own insight in this very life. But such a life is "
"suffering.’"

msgctxt "dn9:71.5"
msgid "Na kho panetaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, evaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr "But you should not see it like this."

msgctxt "dn9:71.6"
msgid ""
"Saṅkilesikā ceva dhammā pahīyissanti, vodāniyā ca dhammā abhivaḍḍhissanti, "
"paññāpāripūriṃ vepullattañca diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharissati, pāmujjañceva bhavissati pīti ca passaddhi ca sati "
"ca sampajaññañca sukho ca vihāro."
msgstr ""
"Corrupting qualities will be given up and cleansing qualities will grow. One "
"will enter and remain in the fullness and abundance of wisdom, having "
"realized it with one’s own insight in this very life. And there will be only "
"gladness and joy, tranquility, mindfulness and awareness. Such a life is "
"blissful."

